Dino, I purchased an old trunk which had been cleaned using buttermilk
on a rag. She had poured it in a pan, and changed rags until they were
no longer &quot;dirty&quot;. I later tried this on a smaller leather case and it
worked well for me. There is no smell once the leather dries, and it
will actually polish a bit with a dry towel.

Not sure about the rusty metal. Good Luck

