&gt; Not sure about the rusty metal. Good Luck

"/> I've cleaned rusty metal with a wire brush to get most of the loose rust
off. Then I wipe with a tack cloth. Then paint the surface with
Rustoleum's Rust Reformer. You can pick this up at a hardware store. About
$7 a squeeze bottle. It's kind of expensive, so use it up before it
thickens. (It's good on your car too!) It seals metal and is like a
primer. Then paint matte black, gloss, whatever you choose.
I don't know if this is *museum* quality restoration for metal, but I like
the results.

Susan
(usually a museum conservator : &gt; )

